[Studio -> /studio]

/// section
h1: About Slab

col:
  p: We started Slab in 2018 after leaving larger agencies because we wanted to do fewer projects, better. Seven people, no junior-to-senior ratio games, no account managers between you and the work.

col:
  p: Everyone at Slab touches client work. Our lead designer also codes. Our strategist also writes. That's on purpose.

/// section align:center
h2: How we work

col:
  icon: bi bi-chat-square-text
  h3: Discovery
  p: Two-week engagement to align on objectives, audiences, and success criteria before any creative begins.

col:
  icon: bi bi-easel
  h3: Creative development
  p: Three rounds of feedback with clear decision points. No endless-revision contracts.

col:
  icon: bi bi-box-arrow-up-right
  h3: Handoff
  p: Full source files, a brand guidelines document, and a 30-day support window after launch.

/// section bg:dark text:light align:center
h2: We work with clients who ship.
p: Not committees. Not approvals-by-committee. Founders, CPOs, and creative directors with the authority to make decisions and the taste to know a good one.
